Subjects: occasional verse; pageant verses; Arthur, prince of Wales; Catherine of Aragon
_description: The speech of Alphouns at the pageant celebrating the marriage between Prince Arthur and Princess Catharine — seven stanzas

BLCottVitAXVI.First Lines: Doughter kateryne I Alphons RemembreCerteyn constellacions passed many a day…
BLCottVitAXVI.Last Lines: …To ffolowe vpon your noble mariageTo prynce Arthurs worthy personage
